Raspberry Pi OCR/TTS Read ME

Prerequisites

before running the code, make sure you have the following libraries and dependencies installed on your Raspberry Pi.

Libraries list:

1. OpenCV (cv2)
   -install using: pip install opencv-python

2. Tesseract OCR Engine
   -install using: sude apt-get install tesseract-oct

3. Tesseract OCR Python Wrapper (pytesseract)
   -install using: pip install pytesseract

4. PICamera
   -install using: pip install picamera[array]

5. Pyttsx3 (Text-to-Speech)
   -install using: pip install pyttsx3

6. NumPy:
   -install using: pip install numpy

7. PySimpleGUI
   -install using: PySimpleGUI

8. Pygame
   -install using: pip install pygame

9. Google Text to Speech (Gtts)
   -install useing: pip install gtts

Notes: Ensure your raspberry Pi has the necessary permissions for camera access and adjust the OCR language and configurations in the `config` variables within the code if needed.
